<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19347] AclControlManager unsafe state update</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19347</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In AclControlManager#createAcls, we are updating the timeline data structures prior to the record being replayed. This could potentially allow uncommitted state to be exposed to callers. In general, this kind of update could lead to data consistency problems, but for ACLs in particular there is actually no problem.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the write side of things, createAcls was making the same update as the replay method and this action is idempotent. This means the end result will be the same. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the read side, the concern is that uncommitted state is acted on and the controller crashes. For ACLs, this actually doesn&apos;t present a problem because we only apply ACLs from AclsDelta which is populated by MetadataLoader. Since MetadataLoader only replays committed records, there is no potential for exposing uncommitted data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regardless, we should fix this unsafe update in the controller.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
